The paper discusses the modeling of microscopic robots for chemical sensing in capillaries, which involves aspects of engineering (cs.ME), nanotechnology (cs.NE), and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper focuses on the interaction between the robots and red blood cells (erythrocytes), which falls under the category of biomedical engineering (cs.BM). Finally, the paper discusses the quantitative performance estimates of the devices, which could be considered a topic in electrical engineering (cs.ET).
